    • Class com.github.btrekkie.programmatic_image.ProgrammaticImageComponent extends javax.swing.JComponent implements Serializable

      serialVersionUID:
      9212293386643020026L

      • Serialized Fields

        • renderer

          IProgrammaticImageRenderer renderer
          The IProgrammaticImageRenderer whose image we are rendering.

        • cache

          ProgrammaticImageCache cache
          The cache for storing different portions of the underlying image.

        • workers

          java.util.Map<K,V> workers
          The ProgrammaticImageWorkers that are currently rendering different portions of the image.

        • scale

          double scale
          The factor by which we are scaling the image.

        • hasInitialized

          boolean hasInitialized
          Whether the component has been "initialized", or properly added to the hierarchy of some frame or window.

        • imageWidth

          int imageWidth
          The width of the images we store in "cache" (although the images at the far right of "renderer" might be narrower than this).

        • imageHeight

          int imageHeight
          The height of the images we store in "cache" (although the images at the bottom of "renderer" might be shorter than this).

    • Class com.github.btrekkie.programmatic_image.ProgrammaticImageFrame extends javax.swing.JFrame implements Serializable

      serialVersionUID:
      -3629792110769252855L

      • Serialized Fields

        • renderer

          IProgrammaticImageRenderer renderer
          The IProgrammaticImageRenderer whose image we are rendering.

        • component

          ProgrammaticImageComponent component
          The ProgrammaticImageComponent that is rendering the image.

        • scrollPane

          javax.swing.JScrollPane scrollPane
          The scroll pane for scrolling "component".

        • baseScale

          double baseScale
          The "base" scaling factor, when scaleLevel is 0. This is unspecified prior to computing it.

        • haveInitializedBaseScale

          boolean haveInitializedBaseScale
          Whether we have set a baseScale value.

        • scaleLevel

          int scaleLevel
          The number of zoom increments we have zoomed in relative to baseScale. The scaling factor is baseScale * Math.pow(SCALE_MULT, scaleLevel).

        • zoomScrollX

          double zoomScrollX
          The current horizontal scroll position, if we are in the process of zooming in or out. This is a negative number if we are not currently zooming in or out. This is expressed as the x coordinate of the center of the visible portion of the scroll content divided by the width of the content.

        • zoomScrollY

          double zoomScrollY
          The current vertical scroll position, if we are in the process of zooming in or out. This is a negative number if we are not currently zooming in or out. This is expressed as the y coordinate of the center of the visible portion of the scroll content divided by the height of the content.
